ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule is in Durban. The MK fighters are calling for the ANC in KwaZulu-Natal to be disbanded, while truckers want government to do something about foreigners they say are taking their jobs. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule says the party will speak to Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula following scathing tweets against MKMVA members. "We will engage with comrade Mbalula, he is a member of the national working committee, and so we will engage with him. READ: Mbalula, Niehaus clash over Prasa on Twitter "I can't engage him publicly here and try and engage what the issues are," said Magashule. On Monday, Mbalula launched a scathing attack on Twitter, labelling MKMVA president Kebby Maphatsoe a coward and spokesperson Carl Niehaus, a thug. READ: Niehaus: Mbalula is young and insulting The Twitter war erupted after the veterans said Mbalula must be held accountable for the collapse of the Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa's infrastructure, which happened the watch of Mbalula. Watch the video above for more on this story.